description: Aben Resources Ltd., an exploration stage company, engages in the acquisition and exploration of mineral properties primarily in British Columbia, Saskatchewan, and Yukon, Canada. The company primarily explores for gold and graphite deposits. Its flagship project is the Forrest Kerr Gold project that covers an area of 23,397 hectares located in northwestern British Columbia. The company was formerly known as Consolidated Abaddon Resources Inc. and changed its name to Aben Resources Ltd. in January 2011. Aben Resources Ltd. was incorporated in 1960 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
